<HEAD>No Damages Awarded for Loss of Bull Semen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLFAX, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The owners of Blitz, a prize bull, should not be compensated for the bull's death or the loss of his valuable semen, a jury has decided. <PERSON> Alvene </PERSON> and <PERSON> Emily </PERSON> <PERSON> Leinweber </PERSON> had sued <PERSON> Ed </PERSON> and <PERSON> Karen </PERSON> <PERSON> Hinnenkamp </PERSON> for $ 150,000, claiming Blitz was fatally wounded in 1983 while defending his herd against a trespassing <ORGANIZATION> Hereford </ORGANIZATION> owned by the defendants. The Leinwebers claimed Blitz was the foundation of their breeding business, <ORGANIZATION> Palouse </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pinzgauer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Breeders </ORGANIZATION>, 11 miles north of <LOCATION> Colfax </LOCATION>. They said Blitz had to be put to sleep months after the alleged fight, since he could n't stand up long enough to have his semen extracted. Blitz's semen cost about $ 20 a sample and was sold throughout the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, the <PERSON> Leinwebers </PERSON> said. The Hinnenkamps acknowledged their bull broke out of its pasture and flirted with <PERSON> Blitz </PERSON>'s cows, but denied it attacked Blitz. After an eight-day civil trial in <ORGANIZATION> Whitman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Superior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION>, jurors decided Wednesday the Hinnenkamps were not liable for their <ORGANIZATION> Hereford </ORGANIZATION>'s rambling, nor were they negligent for not preventing the bull's activity. The decision came despite an earlier plea from the Leinwebers' attorney, <PERSON> Linda </PERSON> <PERSON> Schauble-Ruff </PERSON>, to award damages `` The Leinwebers are approaching their golden years and were looking forward to the -LRB- financial -RRB- comfort Blitz could have given them,'' she told jurors. `` But that ca n't happen now. They've got only 800 units of semen left to hoard.'' <PERSON> Gary </PERSON> <PERSON> Libey </PERSON>, t