aled Monday. Although <ORGANIZATION> McGill </ORGANIZATION> said, `` I trust that the matter will be laid to rest,'' the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Civil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberties </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> is considering asking permission from <PERSON> Fitts </PERSON> to ask a judge to declare the state's criminal libel law unconstitional, state <ORGANIZATION> ACLU </ORGANIZATION> director <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Bates </PERSON> said Friday `` In any event this whole affair points out the need to abolish the criminal libel statute, because it is an invitation to politicians to intimidate and silence their opponents in an attempt to hide the truth,'' <PERSON> Bates </PERSON> said.
