<SECOND>PM-Treasury Bills,0102</SECOND>
<HEAD>Yields Fall on 52-Week Treasury Bills</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Interest rates on 52-week <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> bills fell in the government's latest auction to the lowest level since May. The <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> sold $ 9 billion of the bills at an average discount rate of 7.04 percent on Thursday, down from 7.08 percent at the last comparable auction on June 2. The rates were the lowest since May 5, when the one-year bills sold for 6.74 percent. The new discount rate understates the actual return to investors _ 7.54 percent with a $ 10,000 bill selling for $ 9,288.20.
</TEXT>
