arily starting July 15 and its medium-duty truck assembly line closes from Aug. 5-8. But demand for light-duty trucks is so high that <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION>'s <LOCATION> Pontiac </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> assembly plant will continue production through the Aug. 4 changeover to 1989 models, as will the Pontiac West plant during an Aug. 12 changeover. <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> reports its model changeover shutdowns a week ahead of time. The only plant closed is <LOCATION> Newark </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Del. </LOCATION>, which shut for 16 weeks beginning June 17 for modernization and retooling. The plant, which built the <ORGANIZATION> Dodge </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aries </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Plymouth </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reliant </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> K-cars </ORGANIZATION>, will build the new <ORGANIZATION> Dodge </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Spirit </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Plymouth </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Acclaim </ORGANIZATION> sedans.
